| 2 | **`RandBetween` for non-MO unique IDs** can produce collisions, especially with negative numbers in string concatenation. | 🟡 Medium | Use `GUID()` or a deterministic key derived from the task's own fields. |
| 3 | **`rcpCode` and `TaskType` are both `Text(Value.Type)`** — identical columns. | 🟢 Low | Remove one and use a single column name consistently. |
| 4 | **`Sender` maps to `TransportOrderConsignee`** and **`Recipient` to `TransportOrderConsignor`** — these are semantically swapped (consignee = receiver, consignor = sender). | 🔴 High | Verify the mapping is intentional; if not, swap them. |
